40|$|A Schweizer 1 - 36 {{sailplane}} {{was modified}} for a controlled, deep-stall flight program. This modification allowed the <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer</b> to pivot {{as much as}} 70 deg leading edge down. Ground vibration and flutter testing were accomplished on the sailplane with the <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer</b> in the normal flight and deep-stall flight positions. Test results indicated satisfactory damping levels and trends for the structural modes of the sailplane. The modified sailplane was demonstrated {{to be free of}} aeroelastic instabilities to 83 KEAS with the <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer</b> in the normal flight position and to 39 KEAS with the <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer</b> in the deep-stall flight position. This flight envelope was adequate for the controlled, deep-stall flight experiments...|$|R
