40|$|In {{a never-ending}} quest for {{reducing}} aircraft weight, an attempt {{is made to}} decrease {{the size of the}} <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer</b> of a jet transport {{through the use of a}} stability augmentation system. This work explores the feasibility of reducing the size of the <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer</b> of large transport jets while still maintaining good handling characteristics in the longitudinal mode. The dynamic equations of motion are employed to study the response of an aircraft to various size reductions of the <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer.</b> At the same time, a stability augmentation system is designed to ensure that the aircraft remains stable during flight on exposure to various destabilizing factors...|$|R
